title: Liszt - The Very Best of Liszt (Various, 2006)
description:
The Very Best of Liszt (2006)

		Franz Liszt (1811-1886)



			Composition / (Performers):


1	6 Hungarian Rhapsodies, S359/R441: No. 2 in D minor
	 (Matyas Antal / Hungarian State Symphony Orchestra)
	
2	3 Liebestraume, S541/R211: No. 3: Nocturne in A flat major
	 (Jeno Jando)
	
3	12 Etudes d'execution transcendante, S139/R2b: No. 5 in B major, "Feux follets"
	 (Jeno Jando)
	
4	Annees de pelerinage, 2nd year, Italy, S161/R10b: No. 5. Sonnet 104 by Petrarch
	 (Jeno Jando)
	
5	Mephisto Waltz No. 1, S514/R181, "Der Tanz in der Dorfschenke"
	 (Peter Nagy)
	
6	Piano Concerto No. 2 in A major, S125/R456: Adagio sostenuto assai
	 (Oliver Dohnanyi / Slovak Radio Symphony Orchestra / Joseph Banowetz)
	
7	Annees de pelerinage, 1st year, Switzerland, S160/R10: No. 4. Au bord d'une source (Beside a Spring)
	 (Jeno Jando)
	
8	6 Consolations, S172/R12: No. 3. Lento placido
	 (Philip Thomson)
	
9	Les Preludes, S97/R414
	 (Michael Halasz / Polish National Radio Symphony Orchestra)
	
10	Prometheus, S99/R416
	 (Michael Halasz / Polish National Radio Symphony Orchestra)
	
11	3 Etudes de concert, S144/R5: No. 3 in D flat major, "Un sospiro"
	 (William Wolfram)
	
12	Grandes Etudes de Paganini, S141/R3b: No. 3 in G sharp minor, "La campanella"
	 (Jeno Jando)
	
13	Piano Concerto No. 1 in E flat major, S124/R455: Allegro marziale animato
	 (Oliver Dohnanyi / Slovak Radio Symphony Orchestra / Joseph Banowetz)
	
14	Annees de pelerinage, 3rd year, S163/R10: No. 4. Les jeux d'eau a la villa d'Este
	 (Jeno Jando)
	
15	Harmonies poetiques et religieuses, S173/R14: No. 7. Funerailles
	 (Philip Thomson)
	
16	4 Valse oubliees, S215/R37: No. 1
	 (Peter Nagy)
	
17	Rhapsodie espagnole, S254/R90, "Folies d'Espagne et jota aragonesa"
	 (Xiangdong Kong)
	
18	Schubert - Die Forelle (The Trout), S564/R248 (2nd version)
	 (Valerie Tryon)
	
19	2 Concert Etudes, S145/R6: No. 1. Gnomenreigen (Dance of the Gnomes)
	 (William Wolfram)
	
20	A Faust Symphony, S108/R425: Final Chorus
	 (Andras Ligeti / Franz Liszt Academy of Music Orchestra / Hungarian State Opera Chorus)
	

		"The Very Best of Liszt", retail 2006.

This is the 2CD "very best of" compilation from the naxos series with the cartoonish abomination album covers. The original front cover album art is obviously not embedded, but replaced with decent custom 600x600.

Codec profile is Opus VBR at bitrate 96 (libopus 1.1),
genre marked as Classical - and tracks are as always tagged and pretty.

Support your local naxos dealer.

			enjoy ! /dussin
